895
01:08:32,239 --> 01:08:37,404
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Be very careful giving someone that power over you.

896
01:08:39,880 --> 01:08:41,848
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, thank you.

897
01:08:42,016 --> 01:08:44,177
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yes, thank you for the warning.

898
01:08:46,354 --> 01:08:48,345
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Cheers.

899
01:08:49,090 --> 01:08:51,081
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l cannot claim this next feat as illusion.

900
01:08:51,258 --> 01:08:55,456
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What you're about to see is considered safe.

901
01:09:35,469 --> 01:09:37,664
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The Great Danton.

902
01:09:44,045 --> 01:09:45,706
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l apologize.

903
01:09:45,880 --> 01:09:49,611
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There simply is too much magic...

904
01:09:49,784 --> 01:09:54,778
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...for my stage at the Pantages across the street.

905
01:09:56,157 --> 01:09:58,691
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Bravo! -Bravo!

906
01:09:58,859 --> 01:10:02,260
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pardon my intrusion.

907
01:10:02,930 --> 01:10:05,763
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Bravo! -And go easy on the poor chap.

908
01:10:05,933 --> 01:10:09,027
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He does try so very hard.

909
01:10:11,639 --> 01:10:13,470
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l don't know how Borden found him.

910
01:10:13,641 --> 01:10:15,438
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Kept him under wraps, l was careful.

911
01:10:15,609 --> 01:10:17,543
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yeah, well, he did.

912
01:10:18,379 --> 01:10:19,471
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Do you think it was her?

913
01:10:26,921 --> 01:10:29,549
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You weren't expecting me?

914
01:10:29,723 --> 01:10:32,385
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l was expecting you sooner. Your message said afternoon.

915
01:10:32,560 --> 01:10:34,653
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}lt takes a bit for me to get around these days.

916
01:10:35,162 --> 01:10:36,652
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He's taken everything from me.

917
01:10:36,831 --> 01:10:39,698
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}My wife, my career, now you.

918
01:10:39,867 --> 01:10:40,856
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What do you mean? You sent me...

919
01:10:41,035 --> 01:10:43,902
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l sent you to steal his secret, not to improve his act.

920
01:10:44,071 --> 01:10:45,538
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-That's my job. -Or fall in love.

921
01:10:45,706 --> 01:10:48,266
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-l did everything you asked! -Yes? Yes?

922
01:10:48,442 --> 01:10:50,967
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Then how does he do it? -Cutter was right, a double.

923
01:10:51,145 --> 01:10:54,410
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Of course Borden said that. -He didn't say anything. l've seen things.

924
01:10:54,582 --> 01:10:58,348
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Makeup, glasses, wigs. We don't use it for the show, but l've seen it backstage.

925
01:10:58,519 --> 01:11:02,319
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}lt's misdirection. He leaves things around to make you think he's using a double.

926
01:11:02,490 --> 01:11:04,253
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All the time? He doesn't know when l look.

927
01:11:04,425 --> 01:11:06,393
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All the time, Olivia!

928
01:11:06,560 --> 01:11:08,858
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That's who he is! That's what it takes!

929
01:11:09,029 --> 01:11:11,395
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He lives his act! Don't you see?

930
01:11:13,534 --> 01:11:16,731
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Just because you're sleeping with him doesn't mean he trusts you.

931
01:11:16,904 --> 01:11:19,236
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You think you can see everything, don't you?

932
01:11:19,406 --> 01:11:23,035
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But the Great Danton is a blind fool. His notebook.

933
01:11:25,112 --> 01:11:27,239
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You stole it?

934
01:11:27,414 --> 01:11:29,177
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l borrowed it for tonight.

935
01:11:29,350 --> 01:11:31,375
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l thought you could translate it, but now...

936
01:11:31,552 --> 01:11:32,541
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-l can't. -You can't?

937
01:11:32,720 --> 01:11:35,553
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Olivia, no one can, it's a cipher.

938
01:11:35,723 --> 01:11:38,988
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Even with the keyword it would take months to decode.

939
01:11:39,160 --> 01:11:42,095
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-And without the keyword? -Perhaps never.

940
01:11:42,263 --> 01:11:43,662
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-We'll see. -We will not see.

941
01:11:43,831 --> 01:11:46,766
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}lf l don't get that back to him tomorrow, he'll know l took it.

942
01:11:46,934 --> 01:11:49,095
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Leave him. -l can't. He knows where l live.

943
01:11:50,504 --> 01:11:52,438
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This is his diary, Olivia.

944
01:11:52,606 --> 01:11:55,234
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All of his secrets are right here in my hands.

945
01:11:56,243 --> 01:11:57,471
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Won't bring your wife back.

946
01:11:57,645 --> 01:12:00,808
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l don't care about my wife, l care about his secret.

947
01:12:13,627 --> 01:12:15,424
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Look...

948
01:12:16,597 --> 01:12:18,622
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...l'll go to his workshop and stage a break-in.

949
01:12:18,799 --> 01:12:22,963
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-He'll know you took it. -Yes, me. Not you.

950
01:12:23,137 --> 01:12:24,900
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Understand?

951
01:12:33,447 --> 01:12:34,436
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Robert.

952
01:12:37,017 --> 01:12:39,679
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l have fallen in love with him.

953
01:12:40,688 --> 01:12:43,384
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Then l know how hard this has been for you.

954
01:12:51,765 --> 01:12:53,858
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Notebook?

955
01:12:55,903 --> 01:12:57,768
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Then he's just getting started.

956
01:13:28,235 --> 01:13:29,793
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Good evening. -Professor.

957
01:13:29,970 --> 01:13:32,731
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Professor.

958
01:13:33,207 --> 01:13:36,609
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Here. -Could l get your autograph? -l'm walking tonight. -Professor.

959
01:13:36,677 --> 01:13:38,577
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Let him come. l don't care.

960
01:13:38,746 --> 01:13:41,146
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Professor. -Professor.

961
01:15:05,899 --> 01:15:08,367
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-You all right? -l'm alive.

962
01:15:08,535 --> 01:15:10,628
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Saves me cutting you an air hole.

963
01:15:24,685 --> 01:15:27,176
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-l'm impressed. -Why's that?

964
01:15:27,354 --> 01:15:29,845
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're finally getting your hands dirty.

965
01:15:30,491 --> 01:15:33,187
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}lt's what a good trick costs, Angier.

966
01:15:33,360 --> 01:15:34,691
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Risk.

967
01:15:34,862 --> 01:15:36,090
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sacrifice.

968
01:15:36,630 --> 01:15:40,293
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The sacrifice, l'm afraid, is gonna be yours, unless you give me what l want.

969
01:15:41,602 --> 01:15:43,832
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Which is? -Your secret.

970
01:15:44,371 --> 01:15:46,236
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}My secret?

971
01:15:46,407 --> 01:15:48,671
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Your method for The Transported Man.

972
01:15:48,842 --> 01:15:51,436
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Fallon wouldn't tell me. He doesn't seem to talk at all.

973
01:15:51,612 --> 01:15:52,874
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You have my notebook.

974
01:15:53,046 --> 01:15:54,980
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Useless without the keyword.

975
01:15:56,483 --> 01:15:58,110
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Write down your method, Mr. Borden.

976
01:15:58,285 --> 01:16:00,150
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Describe it in full.

977
01:16:13,233 --> 01:16:15,827
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l want the whole method, not the keyword.

978
01:16:16,003 --> 01:16:18,403
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l don't even know if your secret's in your notebook.

979
01:16:18,572 --> 01:16:20,836
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The keyword is the method.

980
01:16:24,645 --> 01:16:25,805
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Where's my engineer?

981
01:16:33,120 --> 01:16:35,554
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Alive? -How fast can you dig?

982
01:16:38,125 --> 01:16:41,094
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Fallon! You hear me? Fallon!

983
01:16:42,629 --> 01:16:45,063
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-How's the arm? -Still attached.

984
01:16:46,600 --> 01:16:48,932
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Did you find your answer? -Our answer.

985
01:16:49,102 --> 01:16:51,900
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Cutter, l haven't looked yet. l wanted you to share this.

986
01:16:52,072 --> 01:16:54,540
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l already know how he does it, Robert.

987
01:16:54,708 --> 01:16:57,575
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The same way he always has. The same way as we do.

988
01:16:57,744 --> 01:17:00,110
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}lt's just that you want something more.

989
01:17:00,280 --> 01:17:01,838
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, let's find out then, shall we?

990
01:17:07,387 --> 01:17:08,684
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What does it mean?

991
01:17:16,763 --> 01:17:19,027
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}lt means, Cutter, we have a journey ahead of us.

992
01:17:19,199 --> 01:17:21,929
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-To America. -Robert?

993
01:17:22,102 --> 01:17:24,229
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Listen to me.

994
01:17:25,172 --> 01:17:28,539
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Obsession is a young man's game.

995
01:17:28,709 --> 01:17:32,645
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Oh, come on. -l can't follow you any further in it.

996
01:17:33,881 --> 01:17:35,610
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l can't. l'm sorry.

997
01:17:39,920 --> 01:17:41,410
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Then the rest is up to me.

998
01:17:43,524 --> 01:17:45,151
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l'm sorry.

999
01:17:50,364 --> 01:17:54,032
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Good evening. Hello, darling.

1000
01:17:54,201 --> 01:17:55,566
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Champagne, your finest.

1001
01:17:56,303 --> 01:17:58,703
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l didn't know we were going to be joined for dinner.

1002
01:17:58,872 --> 01:18:01,807
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Absolutely. We are celebrating. -Miss Wenscombe.

1003
01:18:01,975 --> 01:18:04,910
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mr. Fallon. Well, what are we celebrating?

1004
01:18:05,078 --> 01:18:07,512
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, we've hit upon a new trick, haven't we, Fallon?

1005
01:18:07,681 --> 01:18:10,582
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-What trick, Freddy? -Yes, Freddy, what trick?

1006
01:18:10,751 --> 01:18:15,017
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l am going to bury myself alive every night...

1007
01:18:15,188 --> 01:18:18,954
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...and then someone will come along and dig me up. Wonderful.

1008
01:18:19,126 --> 01:18:23,028
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-No, l think my husband's had quite enough. -No, pour the champagne. Come on, pour...

1009
01:18:23,196 --> 01:18:25,926
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Right. Sarah, don't talk to me like that. l'm not a child.

1010
01:18:26,099 --> 01:18:28,033
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Perhaps it would... -Perhaps, Mr. Fallon...

1011
01:18:28,201 --> 01:18:31,261
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...you might escort Miss Wenscombe home. My husband's being a bore.

1012
01:18:31,438 --> 01:18:33,531
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-l see no reason why you have to suffer. -Oh, please. Don't ruin this evening.

1013
01:18:33,707 --> 01:18:35,004
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Do not be so disappointing them

1014
01:18:38,478 --> 01:18:42,039
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Good night, Mrs. Borden. Good night, Freddy.

1015
01:18:45,852 --> 01:18:47,979
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-"Freddy"? -Well, that's my name.

1016
01:18:48,155 --> 01:18:52,421
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Not at home. -Well, l'm not always at home, am l?

1017
01:18:53,393 --> 01:18:56,294
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, couldn't you have at least taken off the beard?

1018
01:18:56,463 --> 01:19:00,126
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sarah, l just came from the bloody theater just now.

1019
01:19:00,300 --> 01:19:01,995
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All right? And l'm out in public.

1020
01:19:02,169 --> 01:19:05,297
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Everybody else loves it. -Why are you being like this, Alfred?

1021
01:19:05,939 --> 01:19:08,237
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l had a terrible ordeal today.

1022
01:19:08,408 --> 01:19:13,038
