{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...talking about me that way.

1275
01:39:22,521 --> 01:39:24,512
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-No. -Yes.

1276
01:39:27,893 --> 01:39:32,660
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}lt's inhuman to be so cold.

1277
01:39:37,837 --> 01:39:41,637
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He's back. After two years.

1278
01:39:41,807 --> 01:39:45,470
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He's got a new trick. They're saying it's the best London's ever seen.

1279
01:39:47,813 --> 01:39:51,214
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You should see the look on your face, Professor.

1280
01:39:52,184 --> 01:39:54,049
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You should go to him.

1281
01:39:54,220 --> 01:39:56,586
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You two deserve each other.

1282
01:40:01,694 --> 01:40:05,494
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l'm afraid l'm booked. The Moscow Ballet, they'll be playing through next year.

1283
01:40:05,664 --> 01:40:08,258
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Then get rid of them. There'll be a hundred performances.

1284
01:40:08,434 --> 01:40:10,129
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No more, no less.

1285
01:40:10,302 --> 01:40:12,736
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Five performances a week. No matinees.

1286
01:40:14,640 --> 01:40:17,575
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And that's what you'll be charging for each ticket. Good day.

1287
01:40:40,366 --> 01:40:42,857
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Ladies and gentlemen, my first trick of the evening...

1288
01:40:43,035 --> 01:40:45,697
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...is one that involves considerable risk.

1289
01:40:46,238 --> 01:40:48,900
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Anyone in the audience who would be irrevocably damaged...

1290
01:40:49,074 --> 01:40:52,100
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...by seeing a man drown should leave now.

1291
01:40:52,278 --> 01:40:55,247
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}For when l tell you the young lady who taught me this illusion...

1292
01:40:55,414 --> 01:40:57,006
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...actually died performing it...

1293
01:40:57,182 --> 01:41:00,379
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...you will understand the seriousness of the dangers involved.

1294
01:41:02,621 --> 01:41:04,350
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Let's begin.

1295
01:41:14,733 --> 01:41:18,100
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}ln my travels, l have seen the future...

1296
01:41:19,238 --> 01:41:22,071
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...and it is a strange future indeed.

1297
01:41:22,775 --> 01:41:24,834
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The world, ladies and gentlemen...

1298
01:41:25,010 --> 01:41:30,312
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...is on the brink of new and terrifying possibilities.

1299
01:41:49,601 --> 01:41:54,038
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What you're about to witness is not magic.

1300
01:41:54,206 --> 01:41:55,673
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}lt is purely science.

1301
01:41:56,075 --> 01:41:58,475
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l would like to invite you to come up on-stage now...

1302
01:41:58,644 --> 01:42:01,545
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...so that you can examine the machine for yourselves.

1303
01:42:57,036 --> 01:43:00,199
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Man's reach exceeds his imagination.

1304
01:43:00,372 --> 01:43:01,566
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Bravo!

1305
01:43:04,543 --> 01:43:07,137
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Bravo! Bravo!

1306
01:43:11,417 --> 01:43:14,147
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Bravo. Bravo.

1307
01:43:22,394 --> 01:43:24,055
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}One hundred performances.

1308
01:43:24,229 --> 01:43:26,527
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Why? Does his method dictate that?

1309
01:43:26,698 --> 01:43:28,598
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}ls it a publicity move? What is it?

1310
01:43:28,767 --> 01:43:30,920
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He's a no-talent magician,

1311
01:43:30,921 --> 01:43:33,466
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and they're calling him......the bloody best in England. Why?

1312
01:43:33,639 --> 01:43:36,301
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Fifty yards in a second. ln a second!

1313
01:43:36,475 --> 01:43:39,444
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And all that we know is he uses a trap door.

1314
01:43:39,611 --> 01:43:43,809
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Brilliant. What is going on under that stage?

1315
01:43:43,982 --> 01:43:46,780
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Why can't you outthink him?

1316
01:44:01,500 --> 01:44:03,024
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They do this every night?

1317
01:44:03,202 --> 01:44:06,365
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}After each performance, yeah?

1318
01:44:36,768 --> 01:44:38,360
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We're done.

1319
01:44:39,538 --> 01:44:40,971
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All right?

1320
01:44:42,407 --> 01:44:44,034
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Let him have his trick.

1321
01:44:44,209 --> 01:44:46,643
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l don't need... l don't need his secret.

1322
01:44:46,812 --> 01:44:48,370
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}So...

1323
01:44:49,748 --> 01:44:52,615
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...don't go back there, you leave him alone.

1324
01:44:52,818 --> 01:44:55,981
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Both of us, just leave him alone.

1325
01:44:56,155 --> 01:44:57,622
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We're done.

1326
01:45:06,565 --> 01:45:08,533
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l told you, John...

1327
01:45:08,700 --> 01:45:10,634
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...l don't want you backstage on this one.

1328
01:45:12,504 --> 01:45:14,904
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l would like to invite you to come up on-stage now...

1329
01:45:15,073 --> 01:45:17,200
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...so that you can examine the machine for yourselves.

1330
01:45:46,605 --> 01:45:50,632
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Hey, you, where do you think you're going? -l'm part of the bloody act, you fool.

1331
01:45:59,685 --> 01:46:01,448
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Who was that?

1332
01:46:58,010 --> 01:46:59,034
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hey!

1333
01:46:59,211 --> 01:47:02,703
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Where's the bloody key? Where's the bloody key?

1334
01:47:02,914 --> 01:47:05,144
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The blind man's got it!

1335
01:47:05,317 --> 01:47:08,878
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Where's the bloody key? Bloody drowning!

1336
01:47:18,263 --> 01:47:20,197
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hold on!

1337
01:47:24,636 --> 01:47:25,898
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What have you done?

1338
01:47:47,826 --> 01:47:53,162
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Alfred Borden, you have been found guilty of the murder of Robert Angier.

1339
01:47:53,332 --> 01:47:56,961
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You will be hanged by the neck until dead.

1340
01:47:57,769 --> 01:48:00,761
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}May the Lord have mercy on your soul.

1341
01:48:02,374 --> 01:48:04,171
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mr. Cutter?

1342
01:48:04,910 --> 01:48:06,207
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Owens.

1343
01:48:06,912 --> 01:48:09,073
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, thank you for coming, Mr. Owens.

1344
01:48:09,247 --> 01:48:13,547
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}lt has fallen to me to dispose of Mr. Angier's equipment.

1345
01:48:13,719 --> 01:48:15,311
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But l noticed from this manifest...

1346
01:48:15,487 --> 01:48:18,945
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...that Lord Caldlow has purchased the bulk of the items.

1347
01:48:19,124 --> 01:48:23,060
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mr. Cutter, if you needed to know where to deliver these items, surely you...

1348
01:48:23,228 --> 01:48:26,527
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, no. lt's just there is one particular item...

1349
01:48:26,698 --> 01:48:30,725
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...this item, in fact, that l would like to...

1350
01:48:30,902 --> 01:48:32,893
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-You would like to...? -Buy.

1351
01:48:33,071 --> 01:48:35,005
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Buy yourself? -Yeah, l suppose so.

1352
01:48:36,241 --> 01:48:38,175
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-This is the machine? -Yes.

1353
01:48:38,343 --> 01:48:42,780
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, l'm afraid Lord Caldlow was adamant about purchasing this particular item.

1354
01:48:43,248 --> 01:48:45,944
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Do you think l could talk to Lord Caldlow in person?

1355
01:48:46,385 --> 01:48:48,785
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Out of the question, l'm afraid.

1356
01:48:51,323 --> 01:48:53,086
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Of course...

1357
01:48:53,258 --> 01:48:56,159
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...l suppose if, in the course of your delivery arrangements...

1358
01:48:56,328 --> 01:48:58,762
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...your paths were to cross...

1359
01:48:59,197 --> 01:49:03,099
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-...l can't stop you speaking your mind. -Thank you.

1360
01:49:04,603 --> 01:49:06,798
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Still here, Borden? -For now.

1361
01:49:07,506 --> 01:49:08,495
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Got a visitor.

1362
01:49:08,673 --> 01:49:09,662
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Lord Caldlow.

1363
01:49:10,542 --> 01:49:12,601
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}With a little girl.

1364
01:49:21,119 --> 01:49:22,711
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Jess?

1365
01:49:22,888 --> 01:49:24,378
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hello, my love.

1366
01:49:25,090 --> 01:49:27,957
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}How are you? l've missed you so much.

1367
01:49:28,126 --> 01:49:30,151
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And Fallon's missed you too. We both have.

1368
01:49:30,328 --> 01:49:32,558
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Daddy, can l come in there?

1369
01:49:33,331 --> 01:49:35,697
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Not right now. Not right now, darling.

1370
01:49:35,867 --> 01:49:39,394
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, but everything is gonna be all right.

1371
01:49:39,838 --> 01:49:42,500
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-You must be Lord Caldlow. -Caldlow.

1372
01:49:42,874 --> 01:49:43,966
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yes, l am.

1373
01:49:44,142 --> 01:49:45,302
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l always have been.

1374
01:49:50,382 --> 01:49:52,509
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They flatter you with all those chains, Alfred.

1375
01:49:52,684 --> 01:49:55,653
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Don't they know you can't escape without your little rubber ball?

1376
01:49:55,821 --> 01:49:56,947
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l pulled you out.

1377
01:49:57,122 --> 01:49:58,646
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Out of that tank.

1378
01:49:58,824 --> 01:50:02,487
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All l wanted to do was prove that l was a better magician...

1379
01:50:02,661 --> 01:50:04,526
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...but you couldn't leave me alone.

1380
01:50:06,198 --> 01:50:08,393
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l don't know what you've done...

1381
01:50:10,268 --> 01:50:13,760
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...but you're not afraid to get your hands dirty anymore, are you?

1382
01:50:13,939 --> 01:50:15,770
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, not anymore.

1383
01:50:15,941 --> 01:50:17,169
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And l win.

1384
01:50:17,342 --> 01:50:20,539
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Because no one cares about the man in the box, the man who disappears.

1385
01:50:20,712 --> 01:50:21,701
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You win?

1386
01:50:23,248 --> 01:50:27,651
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This ain't a bloody competition anymore, Angier, this is my little girl's life.

1387
01:50:27,819 --> 01:50:30,879
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And don't you dare put her in the middle of this.

1388
01:50:31,056 --> 01:50:33,889
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, l know how hard it is to have someone so special...

1389
01:50:34,059 --> 01:50:36,687
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...taken away from me, don't l, Borden?

1390
01:50:37,529 --> 01:50:40,157
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And you can't take her with you now, can you?

1391
01:50:40,332 --> 01:50:42,095
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, she'll be looked after.

1392
01:50:42,634 --> 01:50:46,764
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Goodbye, Professor. Come on, darling. -No, no, no. Stop, stop, stop. Look.

1393
01:50:46,938 --> 01:50:48,235
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Here.

1394
01:50:49,708 --> 01:50:51,437
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That's what you're after.

1395
01:50:51,610 --> 01:50:53,703
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That's what this is about.

1396
01:50:53,879 --> 01:50:55,141
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Take it.

1397
01:50:55,313 --> 01:50:57,247
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Your secret? -Yeah.

1398
01:51:00,252 --> 01:51:02,652
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You always were the better magician.

1399
01:51:02,821 --> 01:51:04,311
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We both know that.

1400
01:51:04,489 --> 01:51:08,186
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But whatever your secret was, l mean, you have to agree...

1401
01:51:08,426 --> 01:51:09,450
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...mine is better.

